<% content_for :body_id do %>home-page<% end %>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content">
      <h1>Protect your team with strong encryption</h1>
      <p>Fluidkeys builds on OpenPGP and makes it easy to implement great security across your organisation</p>
      <p>We’re building a better way to do PGP, you can <%= link_to 'test the current release', '#current_release' %> or sign up for release announcements:</p>
      <%= partial "signup_form", locals: { form_id: "header-sign-up" } %>
    </div>
    <div class="illustration">
      <%= image_tag 'github.png', alt: 'Screenshots of signed emails and code commits.' %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pain">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Supporting PGP in a team is time consuming and error&#8209;prone</h2>
      <p>The steep learning curve means supporting new team members is time consuming and costly.
      <p>Keys get out of sync, leading to confusing errors. Verifying, retrieving and refreshing keys is a repetitive, manual process.
      <p>A lack of agreed best practice means lots of keys use old, insecure algorithms. Auditing a team’s keys often gets forgotten.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="illustration">
      <%= image_tag 'pain.jpg', alt: "An illustration of the world of pain and confusion managing PGP." %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="solution">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Automate PGP for stronger, simpler&nbsp;security</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'new-team-member.svg', alt: 'Icon for a new key and backup' %>
      <h3>Onboard new team members</h3>
      <p>Automatically create a key for new starters, along with an encrypted backup and revocation certificate.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'sync.svg', alt: 'Icon for syncronising keys' %>
      <h3>Keep your team in sync</h3>
      <p>Automatically update keys and sync across the team. Starters and leavers are added and removed seamlessly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'best.svg', alt: 'Icon for the best key' %>
      <h3>Audit keys against best practice</h3>
      <p>Use strong ciphers, short expiries and clear certification policies on all the teams' keys.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'imposter.svg', alt: 'Icon for an imposter' %>
      <h3>Look out for imposters!</h3>
      <p>Get alerted for any new keys claiming to be @yourdomain.com</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'signed.svg', alt: 'Icon for signed code commits' %>
      <h3>Enforce Github signed commits</h3>
      <p>Monitor code repositories to ensure all code is correctly signed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <%= image_tag 'rotate.svg', alt: 'Icon for a key with an expiry date' %>
      <h3>Rotate keys periodically</h3>
      <p>Automatically generate new encryption keys every quarter for forward secrecy.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="release" id="current_release">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Current release: 0.3</h2>
      <p>Send end-to-end encrypted secrets from the command line using strong, automatically rotating PGP keys.</p>
      <p class="button"><%= link_to "Download now", "https://download.fluidkeys.com" %></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="progress">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Our progress</h2>
      <div class="card complete">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item checked"><h3>Get started with OpenPGP (v0.1)</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can now create a best practice PGP key from the command line. Fluidkeys backs it up and pushes it into GnuPG so you can start using it right away.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card complete">
        <h3>Level up your legacy keys (v0.2)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">Connect Fluidkeys to your existing key in GnuPG</li>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">Fix issues like weak signatures and out of date preferences</li>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">Automatically rotate your encryption subkey to limit the impact of key compromise</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card complete">
        <h3>Send encrypted secrets (v0.3)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">Send and receive passwords, token and certificates right from the command line</li>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">End-to-end encrypt secrets so only the recipient can read them</li>
          <li class="checklist-item checked">Automatically fetch public keys from a verified email address</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item"><h3>Send sensitive files</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can send files of any size to team mates from the command line. Fluidkeys will handle the encryption, delivery and verify that the file arrived ok.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item"><h3>Synchronise keys across your technical team</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>You’ll be able to add and remove team members and their keys will be automatically synchronised across the whole team.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item"><h3>Level up your git security</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>Your team will be signing git commits, and verifying commits from other team mates. Fluidkeys will configure git for you, and everyone’s keys will be synchronised with Github automatically.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item"><h3>Integrate with Slack</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can use the convenience of Slack with the added protection of end to end encryption. You’ll no longer have to worry about Slack’s security.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card major">
        <ul>
          <li class="checklist-item"><h3>Synchronise keys across your organisation (v1)</h3></li>
        </ul>
        <p>You’ll have a graphical interface for people less familiar with the command line.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="subscribe">
        <p>
          View our <%= link_to "release roadmap on Trello", "https://trello.com/b/dB9j4JaG/fluidkeys?menu=filter&filter=label:release" %>
          or read our <%= link_to "weeknotes", "weeknotes" %>
      </div>


    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="final-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content">
      <p>We’re building a better way to do PGP, you can <%= link_to 'test the current release', '#current_release' %> or sign up for release announcements:</p>
      <%= partial "signup_form", locals: { form_id: "footer-sign-up" } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

